for a n*n matrix
if we want to save the upper triangular matrix in a one-dimensional array, we need the mapping relation between the original matrix and the one-dimensional array
if (i,j) 1≤i≤j≤n
  ∵the index of (i,j) is n+(n-1)+(n-2)+...+(n-i+2) + (j-i)
                        1   2     3         i-1      i+2
  n+(n-1)+(n-2)+...+(n-i+2) = [n+(n-i+2)]*(i-1)/2 = (2n-i-2)*(i-1)/2
  ∴the index of (i,j) is n+(n-1)+(n-2)+...+(n-i+2) + (j-i) = (2n-i-2)*(i-1)/2 + (j-i)
